1172
01:30:04,864 --> 01:30:08,532
<i>by one of the PBR's best.</i>

1173
01:30:08,534 --> 01:30:11,202
<i>Our sports medicine team
are coming in right now...</i>

1174
01:30:11,204 --> 01:30:14,105
<i>to take care of the young man
from North Carolina.</i>

1175
01:30:14,107 --> 01:30:15,874
<i>Talk about your
scary moments.</i>

1176
01:30:15,876 --> 01:30:19,343
<i>The degree of difficulty here
is impossible to calculate.</i>

1177
01:30:19,345 --> 01:30:22,446
<i>The official buck-off time,
4.7 seconds.</i>

1178
01:30:22,448 --> 01:30:24,281
<i>Right now, our medical
staff is attending.</i>

1179
01:30:33,693 --> 01:30:36,294
That's fine, right here.

1180
01:30:36,296 --> 01:30:37,863
No. It's fine, please.
Thanks.

1181
01:30:39,499 --> 01:30:40,432
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1182
01:30:41,801 --> 01:30:43,168
I'll take the bag.

1183
01:30:43,170 --> 01:30:44,369
No, I got it.

1184
01:31:12,432 --> 01:31:13,366
Thank you.

1185
01:31:14,568 --> 01:31:15,901
Luke...

1186
01:31:18,938 --> 01:31:21,907
I'm really sorry.

1187
01:31:21,909 --> 01:31:25,744
I know how hard it must be to give
up that whole part of your life.

1188
01:31:30,784 --> 01:31:31,918
You're kidding, right?

1189
01:31:31,920 --> 01:31:33,319
Sophia...

1190
01:31:33,321 --> 01:31:35,421
You heard the doctors.

1191
01:31:35,423 --> 01:31:36,589
Doctors don't know everything.

1192
01:31:36,591 --> 01:31:38,257
Are you crazy?

1193
01:31:38,259 --> 01:31:39,659
I watched what happened
to you on YouTube.

1194
01:31:39,661 --> 01:31:41,761
You were in a coma
for 10 days.

1195
01:31:41,763 --> 01:31:44,563
I told you, every time a rider
gets in that chute, he could die.

1196
01:31:44,565 --> 01:31:46,532
That's bullshit!
Your situation is different!

1197
01:31:51,538 --> 01:31:53,506
You have to quit!

1198
01:31:53,508 --> 01:31:56,209
You have to!
I can't!

1199
01:31:56,211 --> 01:31:58,511
I can't be with someone if every
time they walk out the door...

1200
01:31:58,513 --> 01:31:59,679
I don't know if I'm gonna
see them again!

1201
01:31:59,681 --> 01:32:01,247
Then that's your choice.

1202
01:32:01,249 --> 01:32:02,615
Yeah, I chose you!
I chose you over New York!

1203
01:32:05,753 --> 01:32:08,422
Over my internship.
I chose you over everything.

1204
01:32:08,424 --> 01:32:09,723
I didn't ask you
to change your life.

1205
01:32:09,725 --> 01:32:11,358
You can't expect me
to change mine.

1206
01:32:15,329 --> 01:32:16,963
This is what I do.

1207
01:32:18,966 --> 01:32:20,834
It's all I know.

1208
01:32:24,372 --> 01:32:26,373
This is my life.

1209
01:32:26,375 --> 01:32:28,508
I thought this was our life.

1210
01:32:30,511 --> 01:32:32,279
I can't watch you ruin it.

1211
01:32:53,434 --> 01:32:54,668
Hi.

1212
01:32:54,670 --> 01:32:56,571
Right upstairs.
Thanks.

1213
01:33:02,544 --> 01:33:03,678
How was...

1214
01:33:06,682 --> 01:33:08,416
How was New York?

1215
01:33:11,520 --> 01:33:12,586
I never made it.

1216
01:33:14,423 --> 01:33:16,557
And I broke up
with Luke anyway.

1217
01:33:18,060 --> 01:33:20,595
I'm really sorry.
Come here.

1218
01:33:20,597 --> 01:33:21,729
Come here.

1219
01:33:30,005 --> 01:33:31,739
How can I help?

1220
01:33:36,780 --> 01:33:38,747
Take my mind off of it.

1221
01:33:41,650 --> 01:33:44,419
What happened after
that fight over Daniel?

1222
01:33:44,421 --> 01:33:46,654
Are you sure you don't wanna
talk about you and Luke?

1223
01:33:46,822 --> 01:33:47,822
Mmm.

1224
01:33:49,024 --> 01:33:50,726
Yeah, I'm sure.

1225
01:33:54,431 --> 01:33:55,931
It's a scary thing.

1226
01:33:57,767 --> 01:34:00,369
How the people
you're closest to...

1227
01:34:01,071 --> 01:34:03,339
can so quickly become...

1228
01:34:04,040 --> 01:34:05,641
strangers.

1229
01:34:33,404 --> 01:34:36,005
I can't do this anymore.

1230
01:34:39,777 --> 01:34:42,077
I'm going crazy.

1231
01:34:46,784 --> 01:34:48,918
I know it's not your fault.

1232
01:34:51,756 --> 01:34:53,156
I have to go.

1233
01:35:38,070 --> 01:35:39,670
No, please don't!
I just need to say something.

1234
01:35:40,705 --> 01:35:41,872
I need to say something.

1235
01:35:48,079 --> 01:35:51,148
I fell in love with you the
first time I saw you.

1236
01:35:51,150 --> 01:35:52,917
You're just the most amazing,
beautiful girl I ever met...

1237
01:35:52,919 --> 01:35:54,585
and somehow...

1238
01:35:54,587 --> 01:35:56,721
I don't know,
somehow you chose me.

1239
01:36:00,026 --> 01:36:02,694
But how I loved you then...

1240
01:36:02,696 --> 01:36:04,596
it's nothing compared to
how I love you now.

1241
01:36:07,500 --> 01:36:09,834
Now, I love you with
everything inside of me.

1242
01:36:10,769 --> 01:36:12,169
I think you should go.

1243
01:36:17,743 --> 01:36:19,144
I love you so much,
I just want you to be happy.

1244
01:36:21,647 --> 01:36:23,882
Even if that happiness
no longer includes me.

1245
01:37:04,858 --> 01:37:07,560
Love requires sacrifice.

1246
01:37:11,131 --> 01:37:12,565
Always.

1247
01:38:18,132 --> 01:38:19,133
<i>And from that day on,
Sophia,</i>

1248
01:38:19,135 --> 01:38:23,805
<i>it wasn't exactly happily ever after,
but it was pretty close.</i>

1249
01:38:26,241 --> 01:38:30,044
<i>We focused on celebrating all
the wonderful things we had...</i>

1250
01:38:30,046 --> 01:38:31,980
<i>rather than regretting
the things we didn't.</i>

1251
01:38:34,216 --> 01:38:35,782
<i>Every anniversary, we would
drive to Black Mountain.</i>

1252
01:38:37,319 --> 01:38:40,254
<i>I still wrote Ruth letters...</i>

1253
01:38:40,256 --> 01:38:41,990
<i>even though I saw her
every day.</i>

1254
01:38:51,634 --> 01:38:52,900
Ruthie.

1255
01:38:57,173 --> 01:38:58,140
Ruth.

1256
01:39:25,168 --> 01:39:27,870
<i>So many wonderful years.</i>

1257
01:39:29,072 --> 01:39:31,141
<i>But, of course,
not nearly enough.</i>

1258
01:39:45,689 --> 01:39:48,357
<i>The paintings Ruth
and I had collected...</i>

1259
01:39:48,359 --> 01:39:51,695
<i>only served as a reminder
of what I had lost.</i>

1260
01:39:53,297 --> 01:39:55,932
<i>So I packed them away.</i>

1261
01:39:58,035 --> 01:39:59,869
Can I help you?

1262
01:39:59,871 --> 01:40:00,937
My name is Andrea McDonald.

1263
01:40:01,972 --> 01:40:03,706
I believe you knew
my husband...

1264
01:40:04,808 --> 01:40:06,308
Daniel McDonald?

1265
01:40:11,048 --> 01:40:14,017
He collapsed in his classroom
early one morning before school.

1266
01:40:14,019 --> 01:40:16,453
A brain aneurysm.

1267
01:40:16,455 --> 01:40:18,788
That was six years ago.

1268
01:40:20,891 --> 01:40:23,093
I'm very sorry to hear that.

1269
01:40:23,095 --> 01:40:24,260
Thank you.

1270
01:40:26,031 --> 01:40:27,998
He was a teacher?

1271
01:40:28,800 --> 01:40:31,235
A professor.

1272
01:40:31,237 --> 01:40:33,303
Physics and astronomy at the
University College London.

1273
01:40:33,938 --> 01:40:35,972
Astronomy.

1274
01:40:35,974 --> 01:40:38,475
I moved back to the States
a few years ago.

1275
01:40:40,277 --> 01:40:42,212
When I saw your wife's
obituary in the paper...

1276
01:40:42,214 --> 01:40:43,214
I knew I had to bring you this.

1277
01:40:49,521 --> 01:40:51,088
It meant a lot to him.

1278
01:41:48,948 --> 01:41:51,316
You did everything you could
with Luke, Sophia.

1279
01:41:52,485 --> 01:41:54,120
You sacrificed.

1280
01:41:56,390 --> 01:41:58,224
I have loved spending
time with you.

1281
01:42:00,293 --> 01:42:02,060
You've made me very happy.

1282
01:42:25,385 --> 01:42:27,220
What are you doing up so late?

1283
01:42:28,955 --> 01:42:30,356
I won tonight.

1284
01:42:31,258 --> 01:42:32,625
Puts me fifth in the world.

1285
01:42:37,497 --> 01:42:38,497
Are you really gonna
start on me now?

1286
01:42:39,499 --> 01:42:40,533
No.

1287
01:42:43,070 --> 01:42:44,570
The mistakes you make
are your own.

1288
01:42:44,572 --> 01:42:46,505
Mistake?
Jesus, Mom!

1289
01:42:49,210 --> 01:42:51,144
These risks you're taking...

1290
01:42:51,146 --> 01:42:52,980
I don't know why.

1291
01:42:52,982 --> 01:42:54,948
I'm just trying to keep
this ranch in the family.

1292
01:42:54,950 --> 01:42:55,916
For you.

1293
01:42:59,887 --> 01:43:01,087
For me?

1294
01:43:01,089 --> 01:43:02,355
Yeah.

1295
01:43:02,357 --> 01:43:03,522
This isn't about me.

1296
01:43:04,892 --> 01:43:06,894
Where are you gonna live?

1297
01:43:06,896 --> 01:43:08,462
If we don't have this place,
where are you gonna go?

1298
01:43:08,464 --> 01:43:11,198
Do you honestly think
I give a damn?

1299
01:43:15,970 --> 01:43:17,638
You're doing this for yourself.

1300
01:43:25,447 --> 01:43:27,015
It's eight seconds.

1301
01:43:28,116 --> 01:43:30,217
That's all it is.

1302
01:43:30,219 --> 01:43:33,620
That girl could be
the rest of your life.

1303
01:44:06,188 --> 01:44:07,455
<i>Sophia Danko?</i>

1304
01:44:07,457 --> 01:44:10,224
Uh, yes. This is she.

1305
01:44:10,226 --> 01:44:14,062
<i>My name is Howie Sanders.
I'm the attorney for Ira Levinson.</i>

1306
01:44:14,064 --> 01:44:15,563
<i>I've been trying
to reach you.</i>

1307
01:44:17,434 --> 01:44:19,234
Uh, yeah. What is it?
Is he okay?

1308
01:44:20,270 --> 01:44:21,971
<i>I'm sorry, Ms. Danko.</i>

1309
01:44:23,173 --> 01:44:25,074
<i>He passed away
late last night.</i>

1310
01:44:30,446 --> 01:44:31,646
<i>Ms. Danko?</i>

1311
01:44:33,048 --> 01:44:34,649
<i>Are you all right?</i>

1312
01:44:34,651 --> 01:44:35,651
Yeah.

1313
01:44:38,154 --> 01:44:41,390
<i>Mr. Levinson's art collection is
being auctioned off next week.</i>

1314
01:44:41,392 --> 01:44:44,293
<i>This is a private auction,
and is by invitation only.</i>

1315
01:44:44,295 --> 01:44:46,462
<i>And Ira asked if
you would attend.</i>

1316
01:44:50,433 --> 01:44:52,334
<i>I know this is short notice.</i>

1317
01:44:53,270 --> 01:44:55,071
<i>But it's important to know...</i>

1318
01:44:56,506 --> 01:44:58,307
<i>he was very fond of you.</i>

1319
01:45:02,012 --> 01:45:03,679
I was very fond of him, too.

1320
01:45:06,449 --> 01:45:08,384
<i>Well, I'll send all the
information along.</i>

1321
01:45:10,253 --> 01:45:12,122
<i>It was nice to finally
talk with you.</i>

1322
01:45:14,558 --> 01:45:15,558
Thank you.

1323
01:45:26,603 --> 01:45:30,040
<i>Tonight we're gonna be watching
the top bull riders in the world.</i>

1324
01:45:31,108 --> 01:45:32,308
Aces.

1325
01:46:42,448 --> 01:46:46,418
<i>This is the one
and only PBR!</i>

1326
01:46:50,857 --> 01:46:55,464
<i>Time to meet your
top 15 contenders!</i>

1327
01:46:56,942 --> 01:47:01,366
<i>Being led out by the number-one-ranked
bull rider in the world...</i>

1328
01:47:01,368 --> 01:47:04,469
<i>from Oklahoma,
Jared Middleton!</i>

1329
01:47:04,471 --> 01:47:07,239
<i>Boy, what a fight
it has been...</i>

1330
01:47:07,241 --> 01:47:10,642
<i>between him and the man
from North Carolina...</i>

1331
01:47:10,644 --> 01:47:12,844
<i>Luke Collins!</i>

1332
01:47:12,846 --> 01:47:15,647
<i>It has been an epic battle
between those two...</i>

1333
01:47:15,649 --> 01:47:18,417
<i>for this title!</i>

1334
01:47:18,419 --> 01:47:22,487
<i>But don't count out men
atop that leaderboard!</i>

1335
01:47:22,489 --> 01:47:24,789
<i>We will now go
atop the shark cage...</i>

1336
01:47:24,791 --> 01:47:28,493
<i>for our
championship-round draft.</i>

1337
01:47:28,495 --> 01:47:31,863
<i>Ryan Dirteater, you will have Smackdown.
We will see you soon.</i>

1338
01:47:31,865 --> 01:47:35,368
<i>Now over to Billy Robinson,
the talent from Virginia.</i>

1339
01:47:35,370 --> 01:47:38,171
<i>Billy, let's find out
what bull you will face.</i>

1340
01:47:38,173 --> 01:47:42,675
<i>You are going to face Bushwacker!
Congratulations!</i>

1341
01:47:42,677 --> 01:47:45,845
<i>Now to the fan favorite from
North Carolina, Luke Collins!</i>

1342
01:47:45,847 --> 01:47:48,781
<i>Luke, your fate
is in that cup.</i>

1343
01:47:48,783 --> 01:47:51,316
<i>It is time for you to reach in
and pull out your bull...</i>

1344
01:47:51,318 --> 01:47:53,186
<i>for this championship round.</i>

1345
01:47:53,188 --> 01:47:55,354
<i>Let's see what it will be.</i>

1346
01:47:55,356 --> 01:47:59,225
<i>Luke, you will have the
number-one contender...</i>

1347
01:47:59,227 --> 01:48:01,294
<i>for this year's World
Champion Bucking Bull...</i>

1348
01:48:01,296 --> 01:48:02,495
<i>Rango!</i>

1349
01:48:24,952 --> 01:48:26,652
<i>Okay, Nashville.</i>

1350
01:48:26,654 --> 01:48:28,822
<i>You know who I'm
talking about.</i>

1351
01:48:28,824 --> 01:48:31,658
<i>With 99 consecutive buck-offs...</i>

1352
01:48:31,660 --> 01:48:34,595
<i>and staring down
number 100...</i>

1353
01:48:34,597 --> 01:48:36,930
<i>this is the number-one-ranked
bucking bull in the world!</i>

1354
01:48:44,372 --> 01:48:46,741
<i>He is doing one of the most
difficult things in sports...</i>

1355
01:48:46,743 --> 01:48:49,576
<i>and that is mounting
a comeback.</i>

1356
01:48:49,578 --> 01:48:53,280
<i>Yeah, but Luke Collins,
he is on PBR fire!</i>

1357
01:49:11,600 --> 01:49:13,034
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

1358
01:49:57,513 --> 01:49:58,781
You got it!
Keep riding!

1359
01:50:21,938 --> 01:50:22,905
Yeah!
Yeah!

1360
01:51:03,948 --> 01:51:06,383
<i>We have just seen
David slay Goliath!</i>

1361
01:51:54,733 --> 01:51:56,934
Hey, Luke, you made
the eight on Rango.

1362
01:51:56,936 --> 01:51:58,035
I knew you were a cowboy.

1363
01:51:59,571 --> 01:52:01,672
One hell of a ride, son, I tell you!

1364
01:52:01,674 --> 01:52:03,575
Luke, we gotta get together
now and talk some business.

1365
01:52:03,577 --> 01:52:05,043
Luke?
Luke, where you going?

1366
01:52:08,881 --> 01:52:10,682
The Levinson artwork
is the largest

1367
01:52:10,684 --> 01:52:13,018
and most valuable
private collection.

1368
01:52:13,020 --> 01:52:15,519
Not only are these pieces sourced
from local Black Mountain College...

1369
01:52:15,521 --> 01:52:17,655
but the world.

1370
01:52:17,657 --> 01:52:19,557
We'll look at contemporary
modern artists...

1371
01:52:19,559 --> 01:52:21,726
such as Andy Warhol, Pat Passlof,
and Willem de Kooning.

1372
01:52:22,728 --> 01:52:24,729
These are amazing works of art...

1373
01:52:24,731 --> 01:52:27,065
and incredibly diverse,
as you already know.

1374
01:52:27,067 --> 01:52:29,768
Never been seen in one place
like this before.

1375
01:52:29,770 --> 01:52:31,236
Thank you,
ladies and gentlemen

1376
01:52:31,238 --> 01:52:33,972
for attending this
remarkable auction.

1377
01:52:33,974 --> 01:52:36,241
If everyone could
take their seats, please.

1378
01:52:36,243 --> 01:52:38,977
I know we are all eager
to get started.

1379
01:52:41,715 --> 01:52:43,882
Before we begin,
a personal note.

1380
01:52:47,753 --> 01:52:50,755
Welcome.
I'm Howard Sanders.

1381
01:52:50,757 --> 01:52:52,824
I was Ruth and Ira
Levinson's attorney...

1382
01:52:52,826 --> 01:52:54,960
for more than 25 years.

1383
01:52:54,962 --> 01:52:57,897
Now, Ira's will
is very detailed...

1384
01:52:58,899 --> 01:53:01,234
on how he wants to
proceed today.

1385
01:53:01,236 --> 01:53:03,569
So, let me start by reading
you a letter he wrote...

1386
01:53:04,671 --> 01:53:05,671
specifically for the occasion.

1387
01:53:07,508 --> 01:53:10,009
"My name is Ira Levinson.

1388
01:53:10,011 --> 01:53:14,813
"I'm an ordinary man who fell in
love with an extraordinary woman.

1389
01:53:14,815 --> 01:53:19,151
"Around this room you will see some
beautiful and priceless works of art.

1390
01:53:19,153 --> 01:53:23,022
"Ruth had an incredible
eye for talent...

1391
01:53:23,024 --> 01:53:25,224
"while I only had eyes for her.

1392
01:53:26,793 --> 01:53:28,594
"For me...

1393
01:53:28,596 --> 01:53:32,298
"the great joy of collecting
wasn't in the art itself... "

1394
01:53:32,300 --> 01:53:34,001
<i>...but in the person
I collected it with.</i>

1395
01:53:34,836 --> 01:53:36,203
<i>My beloved Ruth.</i>

1396
01:53:36,205 --> 01:53:40,107
<i>The happiness these paintings
brought her was immeasurable.</i>

1397
01:53:41,543 --> 01:53:42,575
<i>And sharing that happiness...</i>

1398
01:53:43,777 --> 01:53:45,144
<i>was the great privilege
of my life.</i>

1399
01:53:46,947 --> 01:53:49,115
<i>We celebrated,
we achieved.</i>

1400
01:53:49,117 --> 01:53:51,718
<i>We endured,
we compromised.</i>

1401
01:53:52,120 --> 01:53:53,120
<i>And above all...</i>

1402
01:53:54,022 --> 01:53:55,222
<i>we loved.</i>

1403
01:53:56,624 --> 01:53:58,258
<i>The true work of art...</i>

1404
01:53:58,260 --> 01:54:00,294
<i>was the longest ride
Ruth and I shared.</i>

1405
01:54:01,095 --> 01:54:02,863
<i>This thing called life.</i>

1406
01:54:04,966 --> 01:54:08,335
<i>There's not a painting here I
wouldn't trade in a heartbeat...</i>

1407
01:54:08,337 --> 01:54:10,004
<i>to hear her voice.</i>

1408
01:54:11,806 --> 01:54:13,307
<i>Or see her smile.</i>

1409
01:54:15,343 --> 01:54:17,344
<i>Just one more time.</i>

1410
01:54:17,346 --> 01:54:18,612
Signed, Ira Levinson.

1411
01:54:22,750 --> 01:54:24,818
Thank you all for coming.

1412
01:54:29,625 --> 01:54:31,259
Thank you, Mr. Sanders.

1413
01:54:35,130 --> 01:54:38,600
First up, a painting located on
page 34 of your catalogues...

1414
01:54:38,602 --> 01:54:40,602
<i>titled Portrait of Ruth.</i>

1415
01:54:44,707 --> 01:54:49,944
Composed by American Daniel McDonald,
born 1954, died 2001.

1416
01:54:49,946 --> 01:54:53,881
The work is circa 1963.

1417
01:54:53,883 --> 01:54:56,317
<i>We'll start the bidding at
$1,000 for Portrait of Ruth.</i>

1418
01:54:56,319 --> 01:54:58,987
Do I hear $1,000?

1419
01:54:58,989 --> 01:55:02,758
Who has $1,000 for me?

1420
01:55:02,760 --> 01:55:04,893
How about $800?
Who can give me $800?

1421
01:55:05,829 --> 01:55:07,062
Just $800, folks.

1422
01:55:09,966 --> 01:55:11,199
$600.

1423
01:55:12,167 --> 01:55:13,968
Do I hear $600?

1424
01:55:16,171 --> 01:55:19,707
<i>Who has $600 for Portrait of Ruth,
the first work of the evening?</i>

1425
01:55:20,275 --> 01:55:21,343
$600.

1426
01:55:22,679 --> 01:55:24,980
I have $600.
I have $600, here.

1427
01:55:24,982 --> 01:55:27,049
Going once.

1428
01:55:27,051 --> 01:55:29,952
I have $600.
Going twice.

1429
01:55:31,321 --> 01:55:32,788
Fair warning.

1430
01:55:34,158 --> 01:55:35,691
Sold to the young man
right there for $600.

1431
01:55:44,300 --> 01:55:46,935
Ladies and gentlemen,
we're going to take a short pause.

1432
01:55:46,937 --> 01:55:49,705
We can take this time
to look at the next item...

1433
01:55:49,707 --> 01:55:51,040
which will be a Jackson Pollock.

1434
01:55:51,042 --> 01:55:53,375
That's located on page 124.

1435
01:56:06,057 --> 01:56:07,357
There we go.

1436
01:56:07,359 --> 01:56:08,857
What are you doing here?

1437
01:56:12,162 --> 01:56:13,929
Ira invited me.

1438
01:56:19,804 --> 01:56:21,137
I'm done bull riding, Sophia.

1439
01:56:23,107 --> 01:56:24,874
I'm done.

1440
01:56:27,111 --> 01:56:29,145
Look, I drew Rango
this afternoon.

1441
01:56:31,348 --> 01:56:33,884
I thought if I could just
ride that son of a bitch...

1442
01:56:33,886 --> 01:56:36,220
if I could just make the eight...

1443
01:56:36,222 --> 01:56:37,755
I'd have everything
I ever wanted.

1444
01:56:39,090 --> 01:56:41,157
Well, I did.
I rode him.

1445
01:56:43,194 --> 01:56:44,294
So, you're the best.

1446
01:56:44,995 --> 01:56:46,830
No.
Not even close.

1447
01:56:48,933 --> 01:56:51,001
You see, the whole time
I was thinking about you.

1448
01:56:54,039 --> 01:56:56,774
I realized that what I want is
standing right in front of me.

1449
01:57:16,228 --> 01:57:18,062
What made you buy
that painting?

1450
01:57:19,431 --> 01:57:20,531
Ira.

1451
01:57:26,072 --> 01:57:27,806
Excuse me, sir.
We need you in the other room.

1452
01:57:28,875 --> 01:57:30,342
Sir?
Not now.

1453
01:57:31,878 --> 01:57:33,111
- Sir?
- Not now.

1454
01:57:33,113 --> 01:57:34,179
Mr. Sanders needs you.

1455
01:57:42,421 --> 01:57:44,489
Quiet!
Quiet, please!

1456
01:57:45,224 --> 01:57:46,925
What is your name, son?

1457
01:57:47,960 --> 01:57:49,928
Luke Collins.

1458
01:57:49,930 --> 01:57:51,463
<i>And did you just close your
purchase of Portrait of Ruth?</i>

1459
01:57:52,865 --> 01:57:54,399
Yes.

1460
01:57:54,401 --> 01:57:56,835
Mr. Collins,
I have a stipulation...

1461
01:57:56,837 --> 01:58:00,505
in Ira Levinson's will
I need to read to you.

1462
01:58:00,507 --> 01:58:04,310
<i>"Portrait of Ruth may not be the most
valuable painting in my collection...</i>

1463
01:58:04,312 --> 01:58:06,311
"but it was the most
precious to me...

1464
01:58:06,313 --> 01:58:09,281
"because it reminded me daily
of my beloved Ruth.

1465
01:58:09,283 --> 01:58:11,850
"And so, the terms
of my will are simple.

1466
01:58:11,852 --> 01:58:14,286
"Whoever purchases
the portrait...

1467
01:58:14,288 --> 01:58:16,555
"will receive the collection
in its entirety. "

1468
01:58:18,559 --> 01:58:21,561
Ladies and gentlemen,
this auction is over.

1469
01:58:21,563 --> 01:58:23,262
What?

1470
01:58:23,264 --> 01:58:26,599
This is worth millions.
Millions of dollars.

1471
01:58:26,601 --> 01:58:28,201
How much do you want
for the Warhols?

1472
01:58:28,203 --> 01:58:30,002
What are your plans for
the Jackson Pollocks?

1473
01:58:30,004 --> 01:58:31,270
I have a client who wants
to buy both of the Picassos.

1474
01:58:33,307 --> 01:58:34,974
I'll write you a check.

1475
01:58:38,345 --> 01:58:41,147
Sorry.

1476
01:58:41,149 --> 01:58:44,183
I'm gonna guess that your head
is spinning right about now.

1477
01:58:44,185 --> 01:58:46,619
Yeah.
That's a good guess.

1478
01:58:46,621 --> 01:58:49,155
When your feet
hit the ground, call me.

1479
01:58:50,490 --> 01:58:53,025
You are now
a very wealthy man.

1480
01:59:47,582 --> 01:59:48,582
Hey.

1481
01:59:50,986 --> 01:59:51,953
Hi.

1482
01:59:55,991 --> 01:59:57,558
How was the museum?

1483
01:59:57,560 --> 01:59:59,160
Great.

1484
01:59:59,695 --> 02:00:01,629
How was the ranch?

1485
02:00:01,997 --> 02:00:03,031
Great.

1486
02:00:44,374 --> 02:00:47,443
"Dearest Ruth... "

1487
02:00:47,445 --> 02:00:51,547
<i>When a North Carolina boy meets
a beautiful girl from far away...</i>

1488
02:00:51,549 --> 02:00:55,184
<i>he should do everything
he can to win her over.</i>

1489
02:00:55,186 --> 02:00:58,187
<i>And if he does...</i>

1490
02:00:58,189 --> 02:01:00,089
<i>his life will be
a portrait of happiness.</i>

1491
02:01:11,568 --> 02:01:12,735
What?
Come on!

1492
02:01:15,739 --> 02:01:17,373
Where are you going?

1493
02:01:17,375 --> 02:01:18,674
Come on!

1494
02:01:45,603 --> 02:01:47,337
What took you so long?

1495
02:02:00,433 --> 02:02:06,242
Subtitle:
sync, fix: titler

